The article discusses a conference call with senior administration officials that details legislation going to Congress to strengthen the response to the BP oil spill in the Gulf of Mexico. The legislation includes lifting caps on damages and increasing the amount of money that can be spent on recovery efforts. It also provides assistance to individuals and families affected by the spill, including unemployment assistance, food and nutrition assistance, and help finding work. The bill also includes funding for increased inspections and enforcement of safety regulations on offshore platforms, as well as evaluations of new policies and procedures. The officials state that BP will be responsible for paying for all costs associated with the spill. The legislation is expected to be passed in the next few weeks.